The paper proposes a trajectory calculus for qualitative spatial reasoning, which involves reasoning over moving objects and their paths. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and robotics (cs.RO). The use of answer set programming (ASP) to implement the proposed calculus also suggests a focus on logic-based approaches to reasoning, which is common in the AI and logic programming communities.
